We are currently seeking to appoint a Communications Manager to join us to help shape and define our PR and Social Media Strategy.  The position has the flexibility to be located in our Hong Kong studio.   If you are passionate about working in a dynamic international architectural design practice, we would love to hear from you.

All candidates must have:

Min 8 years’ experience in communications within the architectural/buildings related and/or media industry;
Degree in journalism or communications, English, art, architecture or related fields;
Excellent skills, knowledge and experience in the planning and execution of PR and communication strategies and activities across Mainland China and internationally;
 Experience in social media knowledge experience across all channels (ie. WeChat, LinkedIn, Instagram, Twitter etc…);
Professional manner and approachable, and able to work with initiative and unsupervised;
Ability to  compose well and review media content (write up and visuals for publications, releases and social media);
Proficiency in Microsoft Office packages and Creative Suite software;
 Excellent graphic eye and attention to detail to the execution of press materials;
Fluency in both English and Mandarin Chinese is essential for the role



Please apply by submitting your CV and cover letter stating your location preferences, availability, and salary expectations via the JOIN on our website http://www.10design.co/contact/join OR, apply here.

10 Design is an Equal Opportunity Employer.                                      

www.10design.co

Key Responsibilities

Provide editorial and event management support in all publicity related assignments;
Support the department in English and Chinese editorial needs, including corporate materials and marketing write-ups;
Act as key liaison between external stakeholders and internal departments to ensure communication objective are met;
Supervise the team in day-to-day assignments and manage departmental calendar effectively;
Support building digital capability across the enterprise and act as custodian of all online assets;
Research and collect information on industry and public affairs to keep the company abreast of market developments;
Assist in ad-hoc projects as assigned.

Requirement

Bachelor Degree holder, preferably in Translations, English Studies, Mass Communications or related disciplines;
Minimum 10 years of solid experience in media, corporate communications, public affairs, or research and analysis, preferably in sizable company or news outlet;
At least 2 years’ experience in supervisory role in reputable organization is preferred;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese, conversant in Mandarin is preferred;
Strong PC skills, familiar with creative software is preferable;
Must have solid media experience and proven track record in handling large scale events;
Good interpersonal and communications skills; team player and meticulous;
Candidate with lesser experience will be considered for an Assistant Manager position.

We offer long-term career prospect and competitive remuneration package to the appointed candidate. Please apply in confidence with your detailed resume stating your current and expected salary to Group Human Resources Department

by email to recruit(at)shuntakgroup.com

or mail to Penthouse 39/F, West Tower, Shun Tak Centre, 200 Connaught Road Central, Hong Kong

(Please quote reference number and applied position)

The information supplied by the applicants will be used in accordance with the Personal Data (Privacy) Policy of Shun Tak Group (a copy of which will be provided upon request). Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.


www.shuntakgroup.com

RESEARCH OFFICE

Executive Officer (PR0256/21-22)

The Office is looking for a number of meticulous teamplayers. The candidate will perform the following duties:

Support the University’s research initiatives and enhance its research culture and engagement;
Support the development of the interdisciplinary research labs and the hiring of labs’ members;
Develop and enhance the existing websites and contribute in various social media platforms and external liaison;
Promote research-related events/activities, including but not limited to talks, programmes, conferences, tour visits, interviews, symposiums and exhibitions, etc.;
Provide support in forging industrial/academic partnerships;
Promote research communication and publicity;
Provide support in committee work; and
Carry out ad hoc tasks as assigned.
Applicants should possess:

A recognised degree in Public Relations & Communications, Language Studies or related disciplines preferred;
At least four years of relevant experience;
An excellent command of written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua), and relevant editing and multimedia production skills;
Proactivity, maturity, meticulousness, readiness to accept challenges, capability in multitasking and independence at work;
Strong communication and interpersonal skills, good analytical ability and a strong sense of responsibility;
Ability to work under tight timelines; and
Proficiency in a wide range of computing applications.
Initial appointment will be offered on a fixed-term contract of 2 years. Re-appointment thereafter will be subject to mutual agreement.

Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience.

Application Procedure:

Applicants are invited to submit their applications at the HKBU e-Recruitment System (jobs.hkbu.edu.hk). Those not invited for interview 8 weeks after the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. Details of the University’s Personal Information Collection Statement can be found at http://hro.hkbu.edu.hk/pics.

The University reserves the right not to make an appointment for the post advertised, and the appointment will be made according to the terms and conditions then applicable at the time of offer.

Closing date: 27 January 2022

The Roles

Coordinate, execute and support a variety of corporate and marketing communications activities, public relations and promotion initiatives;
Drive and deliver a range of marketing communication materials, including but not limited to speeches, press release and media kit, corporate collaterals and enewsletter, editorial and publishing projects, marketing and social media content, surveys and research, etc.;
Monitor and uphold branding and corporate identity of HKDC and its affiliated programmes;
Manage corporate assets including printed collaterals, digital, visual and video content and online platforms e.g. website, social media channels and email database;
Work with internal and external parties for the production of HKDC Annual Report, publications and marketing collaterals;
Effectively handle the logistics and coordination of corporate visits and and provide onsite support to corporate events / activities;
Work with internal stakeholders and external parties and vendors on a variety of HKDC initiatives;
Manage the overall communication plan and logistics of the corporate membership and partnership programmes; and
Carry out other ad hoc projects and duties as assigned.

  Requirements

University graduate in Marketing, Communications, Journalism or Translation;
Minimum 5 years of relevant work experience in marketing, corporate communications or public relations;
Excellent copywriting and translation skills in both English and Chinese, with fluent spoken English, Cantonese and Putonghua;
Digital savvy, creative and passionate about communications, with sound knowledge of different social media and communications platforms and trends;
A self-motivated team-player with strong attention to detail; and
Mature, outgoing multi-tasker with good organisational and project management skills.


Interested parties are invited to apply by sending your resume with full details of education, work experience, current & expected salary, contact telephone number and earliest available date to the Human Resources Office, Hong Kong Design Centre, Unit 602, 6/F, Mill 5, The Mills, 45 Pak Tin Par Street, Tsuen Wan or by clicking “Apply Now” or email to: hr[@]hkdesigncentre.org on or before 28 January 2022. HKDC reserves the right not to make appointment for the post(s) advertised. Only short-listed candidates will be notified. All information received will be kept in strict confidence for six months and data will only be used for recruitment purpose.

You will be a team member under Public Engagement stream in Communications and Public Affairs Department of the Authority.
You will be responsible for:
organizing events/programmes for youth engagement and community outreach of the District;
coordinating with arts and cultural programme partners, District Councils, community groups, NGOs or other government organizations for public engagement community outreach collaborations;
liaising with external and internal stakeholders for organizing events and delegation visits;
working with external agencies, outsourced vendors and community partners on public engagement and community outreach initiatives as necessary; and
driving and executing ad-hoc communications projects when required.
You should:
possess a recognized university degree or above in Public Relations, Journalism, Communications or related discipline;
have 3-5 years of relevant and solid experience in in corporate social responsibility, community engagement public relations, events management, media relations and corporate communications;
have solid experience in engaging government bodies, District Councils, NGOs and community groups;
have strong interpersonal and communications skills, good team player, multi-tasking, able to meet tight deadlines and work under pressure, creative and dynamic;
able to execute projects independently with guidance to achieve the engagement objectives and demonstrate strong attention to details and have a flexible approach to work;
have excellent written and spoken English and Chinese; proficient in Putonghua will be an advantage; and
able to work irregular hours at weekends and public holidays if required.
For interested parties, please submit your application with detailed CV on or before 26 January 2022. Applicants are encouraged to submit their applications as soon as possible.  The review of applications will continue until the post is filled.
Data collected will only be used for job application processing. Your data may be accessed by our appointed recruitment consultants who have agreed to keep confidence of all personal data in not less than the standards applicable to us. Applicants not being invited for interview within 4 weeks from the submission date may assume their applications unsuccessful.
All related information will be kept up to 24 months and all personal data will be destroyed afterwards.
For more information
http://www.westkowloon.hk or contact
Ms. Yuki Ha at 2200-3786

You will be a team member under Public Engagement stream in Communications and Public Affairs Department of the Authority.

You will be responsible for:

assisting in developing public engagement strategy and driving community outreach initiatives so as to enhance the public understanding of the work of the Authority and foster support from local community;
planning, leading and organizing community outreach programmes and initiatives of the District;
cultivating relations and liaising with government organizations, arts and cultural programme partners, and NGO/community groups;
coordinating communication materials for Consultation Panel and liaising with the Working Group under Consultation Panel on youth and community engagement initiatives and programme review;
