JOCKEY CLUB DESIGN INSTITUTE FOR SOCIAL INNOVATION
Community Engagement Officer (Ref. 22011406-E)
Jockey Club Design Institute for Social Innovation is a unit aims at providing an innovative and human-centred platform to envision a better life in the society, connecting people with passion and nurturing doers of all ages to innovate with collective wisdom to enable impactful action. 

Duties
The appointee will be required to:
(a) formulate and execute effective marketing programmes;
(b) organize events including preparation of promotion and event materials, pre-event logistic arrangements, on-site event management, etc.;
(c) work closely with internal and external parties to facilitate the smooth implementation of marketing activities;
(d) manage the digital communication channels, including website, social media, etc.;
(e) assist in the development of the Institute’s publicity, corporate branding and image-building;
(f)  engage a spectrum of community groups including senior citizens and non-governmental organizations; and
(g) perform any other duties as assigned by the Director of the Jockey Club Design Institute for Social Innovation and the Project Managers.
Qualifications
Applicant should:
(a)  have a recognised degree, preferably in Marketing, Communications, Advertising, Journalism or related disciplines;
(b)  have at least five years of marketing and communications experience;
(c) have an excellent command of both written and spoken English and Chinese, including Putonghua;
(d) have good communication, liaison and organizational skills;
(e) be a good team player with a strong sense of responsibility and capable of handling multi tasks;
(f) be highly motivated with strong initiatives, innovative and attentive to details;
(g) demonstrate the ability to work under pressure;
(h) have proficiency in MS Office applications, contemporary design applications (e.g. Adobe Photoshop and Illustrator, etc.) and Chinese word processing; and
(i) have strong media network in local news or feature pages being an advantage.
Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.
Application
Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now"  Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms.  If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process.  Consideration of applications will commence on 21 January 2022 until the position is filled.  The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.
PolyU is an equal opportunity employer committed to diversity and inclusivity.  All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to gender, ethnicity, nationality, family status or physical or mental disabilities.

The Job:

Develop corporate communications and public relations plans aligning with the company’s vision, missions and development strategies;
To initiate corporate communications, PR and CSR strategies, generate creative ideas and implement effective campaigns to enhance corporate image and brand awareness, and responsible for management profiling;
Oversee corporate branding as the brand gatekeeper of the bank;
Responsible for the content strategies and development of all PR and corporate materials, including corporate website and social media (wechat, Facebook, Youtube etc), group newsletters, press materials, corporate communication materials including but not limited to corporate presentation deck, video, corporate premiums and so on;
Assist in handling international and China media enquiries and follow up interviews’ opportunities;
Build and maintain strong relationships with media and business partners as well as internal stakeholders;
Work closely with the team on media sponsorship opportunities, including top industry award submissions;
Lead planning on advertising and SEO initiatives to maximize corporate/product branding in the market;
Work on crisis management to develop communications and timely reaction plan whenever necessary;
Work closely with partnership and events team to organize signature group events and support in areas like management speeches, onsite support and press relations;
Assist in team building and manage PR agencies, budget and expenses;
Ensure that all regulatory and legal & compliance requirements and standards are met;
Create a cohesive content and campaign strategy for employee engagement;
Provide strategic guidance and solutions to firm management and other internal clients on internal communications strategies;
Develop and oversee intranet stories, office communications, posters and digital signage and staff events, etc.

Requirements:

Over 8 years of professional corporate communications and PR experience, with strong media, columnists and KOLs in financial sectors in HK, mainland China and international;
Excellent writing and oral communication skills in both Chinese and English is a must;
Crisis management experience in financial sector is preferred;
A good team leader and player with exceptional interpersonal skills;
Degree holders in communications, journalism, business administration, or marketing preferred;
Can work well in a dynamic, rapidly changing workplace; mature and flexible with entrepreneurial mind-set and can-do attitude;
Strong Chinese writing skills in financial sector are required.

We provide attractive remuneration package and fringe benefits for the right candidate. Interested parties please send detailed resume with current and expected salaries to Human Resources Department i) by mail: 22/F, Li Po Chun Chambers, 189 Des Voeux Road Central, HK; ii) by fax: 2537 5431; or iii) by using "APPLY NOW".

Please quote the reference in the application. If application is submitted in hard copy format, it should be placed in a sealed envelope marked “Confidential”. All applications will be treated in strict confidence and personal data provided by job applications will be used for recruitment purposes only. A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be available upon request.

Established in 2009, Hong Kong Green Building Council (“the Council”) is the leading body, co-founded by four major construction industry and environmental organisations, driving the market transformation towards green and sustainable buildings in Hong Kong through engagement with the industry, the government and broader community.
HKGBC is expanding its secretariat team in line with its positioning as Hong Kong's leading member-based body dedicated to green building development, with opening for the post of Project Executive:
Key Roles:
Report to the Head of Marketing, Project Manager and Senior Project Executive;
Coordinate with internal departments, external parties and schools for organising and executing various public education events, trainings, tours and workshops;
Support the preparation of promotional materials including videos, training kits, presentation materials, advertorials and proposals for school engagement activities;
Assist the planning and implementation of online and offline promotional campaigns;
Liaise with vendors including consultants, PR agencies, production houses, etc. to ensure quality and timeliness of deliverables for events and campaigns;
Support all reporting, invoicing and logistics works;
Perform any other duties as assigned.
 Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree holder in Communications, Marketing, Public Relations or related disciplines with minimum 2 years relevant working experience.
Excellent command of both written and spoken English and Cantonese. Fluency in Mandarin would be an advantage;
Grade C or above in Use of English in HKALE and Grade C (Syl. B) / Level 4 or above in English in HKCEE or Grade 5 or above in English in DSE would be an asset
Detailed-mined, versatile and naturally outgoing with strong communication skills
Ability to work both independently and collaboratively with the team;
Self-motivated with a strong sense of responsibility and able to work under pressure;
Proficient in PC applications including MS Office, Chinese word processing and database management;
Knowledge of Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator and Dreamweaver would be an advantage.  
 How to Apply
The Council is an equal opportunity employer and offers attractive career prospects and remuneration to our staff. Recruitment will be initially under contract terms from commencement date to 30 June 2023. Interested applicants please apply by sending full resume with date of availability, present and expected salary, contact telephone number, as well as results of public examinations to the Executive Director, Hong Kong Green Building Council via e-mail careers@ hkgbc.org.hk, or by post to 1/F, Jockey Club Environmental Building, 77 Tat Chee Avenue, Kowloon Tong, Hong Kong. Please state the position you want to apply for on the envelope.
(N.B. Application with incomplete information as requested above may not be considered.)
Applicants who do not receive a response within six weeks from the date of this advertisement may consider their applications filed for future reference. Personal data will be used strictly for recruitment related purposes only and retained for no more than six months.

KNOWLEDGE TRANSFER AND ENTREPRENEURSHIP OFFICE

Project Officer (two posts) (Ref. 22011403-JCS)

Duties

The appointees will work under the Branding and Marketing Division and be required to:

(a) implement and organize marketing events and activities, such as banquets, ceremonies, seminars, conferences, competitions, exhibitions, press conferences, delegation visits, etc.;

(b) liaise and coordinate with relevant parties to ensure successful delivery of projects;

(c) provide administrative support to the University’s societies, committees, trade associations and meetings;

(d) maintain website and social media channels;

(e) prepare reports and project documentations including proposals and budget; and

(f) perform any other duties as may be assigned by the Director of the Office or his delegates.

Working on irregular hours including evenings, Saturdays and Sundays, and occasional travel outside Hong Kong may be required.

Qualifications

Applicants should:

(a) have a recognized degree preferably in Communication, Marketing or Event Management, plus at least three years’ relevant post-qualification working experience; or a recognized certificate or diploma or an equivalent qualification preferably in the said disciplines plus at least five years’ relevant post-qualification working experience;

(b) have sound knowledge of computer software applications, preferably with knowledge of and experience in MS Office applications;

(c) have a good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese, with fluency in Putonghua being an advantage;

(d) have good planning, organizational and problem-solving skills;

(e) be attentive to details and a good team player;

(f) be able to work independently and meet tight deadlines; and

(g) have good interpersonal and communication skills.

Shortlisted candidates will be invited to sit for a written test.

Applicants who have responded to the previous advertisement need not re-apply.

Remuneration and Conditions of Service

A highly competitive remuneration package will be offered.  Appointment will be on a one-year gratuity-bearing contract.   Applicants should state their current and expected salary in the application. 

Application

Please send a completed application form by post to Human Resources Office, 13/F, Li Ka Shing Tower, The Hong Kong Polytechnic University, Hung Hom, Kowloon, Hong Kong or via email by clicking "Apply Now". Application forms can be downloaded from https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/forms. If a separate curriculum vitae is to be provided, please still complete the application form which will help speed up the recruitment process. Consideration of applications will commence on 21 January 2022 until the positions are filled. The University’s Personal Information Collection Statement for recruitment can be found at https://www.polyu.edu.hk/hro/careers/guidelines_and_forms/pics_for_recruitment.

